A more concise way to achieve the desired output is to use [`Arrow Functions`][1]:

&lt;!-- begin snippet: js hide: false console: true babel: false --&gt;

&lt;!-- language: lang-js --&gt;

    const accum = (s) =&gt; s.toUpperCase()
                          .split(&quot;&quot;)
                          .map((s, i) =&gt; s.repeat(i + 1));
                          
    console.log(accum(&quot;abcd&quot;));

&lt;!-- end snippet --&gt;


  [1]: https://developer.mozilla.org/en-US/docs/Web/JavaScript/Reference/Functions/Arrow_functions

You can use `forEach` or `map` both work perfectly as iterator

